body:
> @caybro could you lend a hand to @mprakhov . He's a bit stuck on figuring out why when commenting out unloading the Loaders, there is a weird behaviour where the wrong chat section appears or not everything changes. Maybe you guys could pair on this?

There's 2 things in AppMain.qml if I remember correctly;
- around line 870:

```qml
delegate: Loader {
  readonly property string sectionId: model.id
  active: sectionId === appMain.rootStore.mainModuleInst.activeSection.id
  ...
```

- which has to match the "active section id" further up in the stack layout (around line 690):
```qml
                    currentIndex: {
                        const activeSectionType = appMain.rootStore.mainModuleInst.activeSection.sectionType

                        if (activeSectionType === Constants.appSection.chat)
                            return Constants.appViewStackIndex.chat
                        if (activeSectionType === Constants.appSection.community) {
                            for (let i = this.children.length - 1; i >=0; i--) {
                                var obj = this.children[i]
                                if (obj && obj.sectionId && obj.sectionId === appMain.rootStore.mainModuleInst.activeSection.id) {
                                    return i
                                }
                            }
```

@mprakhov does that help?

@caybro Not much.
For the fix - we need to disable unloading the ChatLayout from the loader when we switch between the sections. For this purposes, we remove changing `active` for Chat section and for Community section... and here is where the magic comes:
If you'll start switching between Chat or community sections - ChatLayout does not update its content, while StackLayout index is changing

@mprakhov you have to make sure this part gets re-executed everytime the section becomes active:

```qml
Component.onCompleted: {
  // we cannot return QVariant if we pass another parameter in a function call
  // that's why we're using it this way                                          
  appMain.rootStore.mainModuleInst.prepareCommunitySectionModuleForCommunityId(model.id)
                                            rootStore.chatCommunitySectionModule = 
  appMain.rootStore.mainModuleInst.getCommunitySectionModule()
}
```
